57e x99 hf y862 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 24:12-49 </div><div class="t m57f xb3 hf y862 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke 24:50-53: </div><div class="t m6f x7f hf y4ae ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Acts 1:1-11 </div><div class="t m580 x6f hf y4ad ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Acts 1:12-26 </div><div class="t m1d0 x24 hf y959 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Burial and </div><div class="t m60 x16 hf y95a ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Resurrection </div><div class="t m19a x5a hf y95b ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Doubt and </div><div class="t m581 xab hf y95c ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Belief </div><div class="t m582 xb3 hf y95d ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Ascension </div><div class="t m7e x75 hf y95d ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Waiting in Prayer </div><div class="t m216 x79 h2f y62 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sabbath in the </div><div class="t m16c x16 h2f y834 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tomb; The One </div><div class="t m2c0 x16 h2f y759 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">who lives </div><div class="t m1e6 xd6 h2f y61 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The walk to </div><div class="t m1b6 x9b h2f y95e ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Emmaus; </div><div class="t m3b9 xd6 h2f y759 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Touch Me </div><div class="t m583 x2c h2f y835 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and see&quot; </div><div class="t m236 x71 h2f y61 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Instruction in </div><div class="t m1e0 x4c h2f y95e ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the kingdom; </div><div class="t m296 x6e h2f y95f ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;This same </div><div class="t m584 x1d h2f y960 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Jesus&quot; </div><div class="t m2eb x75 h2f y61 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">At prayer together; </div><div class="t m1d6 x64 h2f y95e ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Matthias chosen </div><div class="t m421 x21 hf y961 ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">INTRODUCTION: </div><div class="t m3e9 x5a h2f y961 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke&apos;s Gospel closes with the triumph of the resurrec-</div><div class="t m4e9 x21 h2f y962 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tion and the ascension of the Son of man. The disciples, following the in-</div><div class="t m1ee x21 h2f y72 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">struction of their Lord, waited for the Spirit. </div><div class="t m46a x6c h2f y963 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The Acts of the Apostles continues the story of Jesus. In one sense, how-</div><div class="t m4ed x21 h2f y964 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">ever, we might rightly call this book the Acts of the Holy Spirit. All that </div><div class="t m1ad x59 h2f y801 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">happens in Acts happens because Jesus is at God&apos;s right hand. </div><div class="t m11f x6c h2f y965 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Luke also dedicates this book to Theophilus as part of his continuing his-</div><div class="t m249 x59 h2f y966 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">torical record. Much evidence exists that Luke and Acts came from the one </div><div class="t m11a x59 h2f y967 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">masterly mind, including: </div><div class="t m224 x8 h2f y968 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m1ad x7a h2f y968 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Style and language. </div><div class="t m22a x8 h2f y969 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t m103 x7a h2f y969 ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Sympathy for a ministry that reaches all nations and transcends social </div><div class="t m1a2 x7a h2f y96a ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">barriers. </div><div class="t m4c x8 h2f y96b ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t m1c9 x7a h2f y96b ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Defense of Jesus and the Christian church against false charges. </div><div class="t m2bc x8 h2f y96c ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m27f x7a h2f y96c ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Agreement on details in both books. </div><div class="t m340 x8 h2f y96d ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t m175 x7a h2f y96d ff4 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Common themes in the two books. </div><div class="t m100 x5d hf y96e ff1 fs4 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">73 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.0